title: Kueter Credits Kids, Staff For Record
text:
Kueter Credits Kids, Staff For Record October 12, 2015, 1:00 PM by Matt Holsen SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
After 33 seasons, O'Gorman's Steve Kueter is now the winningest high school football coach in South Dakota history. 
The Knights cruised past Rapid City Stevens on Friday for Kueter's 285th victory. There was plenty to celebrate after the game. While his name will be attached to the record mark for years to come, he gives all the credit to his players and staff from more than three decades of O'Gorman football. 
"I'm really proud of everybody involved with O'Gorman high school. I think they can be very proud that as a group we were able to achieve this. It just feels really good," Kueter said. 
Kueter passes Yankton's Max Hawk on the most wins list. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
